  "market_context": "GBP/USD on the 60-minute chart around 10 January 2024, with price reaching into a breaker block and fair value gap below an old low near 1.26844, with SMT divergence visible against a correlated pair.",
  "key_observation": "Price sweeps a low into a breaker block / fair value gap with SMT divergence, displaces higher to form an order block, then closes through it to create a propulsion block that respects its mean threshold on retest.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify SMT divergence between GBP/USD and a correlated asset at the swept low near 1.26844, alongside displacement and a breaker block.",
    "Step 2: Watch price reach into the breaker block, sweeping the resting low into a fair value gap below an old low.",
    "Step 3: Confirm displacement out of that zone, marking the down-close candle that reacted off the level as the order block.",
    "Step 4: Wait for a close back over that down-close candle, which then forms a propulsion block.",
    "Step 5: Require price to retest the propulsion block while respecting the opening price and not closing below its mean threshold.",
    "Step 6: Plan an entry at the propulsion block's opening price, stop on the other side of the body, targeting buy-side liquidity above."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price respected the mean threshold of the propulsion block and displaced higher, delivering to the buy-side liquidity target.",
  "lessons": "A propulsion block forms when price closes through an order block that reacted off a prior level; entries at the opening price with stops beyond the body, validated by SMT and mean-threshold respect, offer high-probability targets to opposing liquidity.",
